Papa Rays Seafood Gumbo Recipe 😮‍💨🔥

•Prep Time: 30 mins
•Cook Time: 2 hour 30 mins

📝 Ingredients:
•Vegetable oil
•All purpose flour
•Holy Trinity (Diced yellow onion, Diced bell pepper ,Diced celery, minced garlic & Chopped parsley)
•Smoked Turkey necks 
•Chicken gizzards
•Chicken Wings & Legs 
(or whatever part you like)
•Sausage of Your Choice (Sliced)
•chicken bouillon
•Dried Bay leaves 
•Seasoning Salt
•Onion Powder 
•Garlic Powder 
•Papa Rays All Purpose Seasoning •Cayenne pepper
•Shrimp (fully peeled and deveined)
•Blue Crabs (fresh or frozen)
•Boiled Eggs (Optional)
•Cooked white rice for serving 

Cooking Instructions:

1️⃣ In a Black pot or Dutch Oven heat the vegetable oil over medium heat. Add the flour and stir continuously to make a roux. Cook the roux until it reaches a dark brown color, Be careful not to burn it. Takes anywhere from 20 minutes to an hour.

2️⃣ Add the holy trinity to the roux. Cook for about 10 minutes, or until the vegetables become tender.

3️⃣ Add Roux to a gumbo pot with water already boiling  and stir until all lumps are gone.

4️⃣ Add All The Seasonings Mentioned (To Your Liking).

5️⃣ Drop in the sliced sausage, Smoked Turkey Necks & chicken Gizzards then cook for 45 minutes.

6️⃣Stir then Add chicken to the pot for 30 minutes, or until chicken selection is tender.

7️⃣ Drop in the blue crab, cook for an 5 minutes or until it is cooked.

8️⃣ Drop in peeled boiled eggs and clean shrimp then cook for 5 minutes.

9️⃣ Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed for your liking, adding seasoning salt, pepper, & chicken buillon if desired, then turn off. 

🔟 Let Gumbo Rest for 2-3 mins then skim all grease off the top & DIG IN.
